summary_to_eng: Resets when trying to call
Text_Summa: Resets when trying to call Regarding the problem described in the ticket: December 23 - the operators said that the situation with outgoing drops has improved (for megacom and beeline). Problems remained only with outgoing to the window - which are still being dropped. To test this; me and [~alexeagro] checked the sims in all channels and dragged sims from different slots to find the problem.Since Oshka is a more popular operator; we decided that it is better to turn off one of the 3 beeline channels (since the beeline is used less in our country) and connect another channel to Oshka so that there are 3 of themThis problem manifests itself when all outgoing channels are busy and the operator tries to make an outgoing call

summary_to_eng: Prepare works for AWS settings
Text_Summa: Prepare works for AWS settings Today I was able to catch our devops and discuss with him about the expected actions for setting up automatic deploying and transferring data to the server. We came to the decision that we need to update the documentation for raising the local server; describe the processes for pushing changes to the staging. I took time out for this weekend for this issues. In the future; we may need to customize the processes of billing on aws; to select a more appropriate strategy for using servers on Amazon. Our devops are worried that older developers who no longer participate in the development process have access to the server; he asked to check it and remove them from aws if they are no longer needed; as this is dangerous.https://gist.github.com/M1rotvorez/98ebd55cccf6b7d98abeadb0285077bd - this is link to gist of documentationhere is the script which checks changes in the /var/www/html directory; deploy-changes.sh:next little task was to fix ssl on staging and set up second vhost on staging for the old version of the project. decided to use docker to fix everything at once.next i've created small dockerfile with apache-php which supports laravel; dockerfile:https://staging.lumici.co.uk/

I suggest to treat invalid / expired tokens as expired. End user doesn't understand what JWT is and why its malformed / corrupted and thus should be redirected to login page. For simplicity's sake let's treat empty Authorization token as 400 and corrupted / malformed; expired as expired and return 401. Is it possible?

summary_to_eng: HR onboarding documents
Text_Summa: HR onboarding documents # In case; when HR didn't create Onboarding flow; what do we need to show if HR goes to the *Onboarding page*? [https://app.zeplin.io/project/5da0b93b5b79ea3080736e84/screen/5da4383974c7950852aec904|https://app.zeplin.io/project/5da0b93b5b79ea3080736e84/screen/5da4383974c7950852aec904]The contract only loads HRIf the HR document is uploaded; it will be automatically approved.When deleting a step in the wizard; a standard pop-up confirmation.All documents with the Approved status are filled out; a new item is added by HR - the teacher will receive the Onboarding status.The teacher cannot delete the uploaded document; only download it. We can re-upload (in the Reject status if the document).Alerts for teachersNotification text: <Teacher> made a change to the file (link to the teacher's profile and automatically scroll the page)For now; link onboard steps to one HR. Only one user with the HR role is created for each organization.Call results:After calling Vlad and Roma about the documents uploaded by the teacher; they came to the conclusion that it would be faster and easier to accept the formula one step = one document. Need to fix the styles. The notification becomes read after clicking on the link. Also need to add a download icon when notifications are fetching. Discussed about notification messages. summary_to_eng: Copy and Paste from local computer
Text_Summa: Copy and Paste from local computer When copying files from local computers clipboard stores only filepath on a drive and pasting on Canvas would do nothing. Because we don't have actual file in clipboard and don't know its type. To do it we need to implement some kind of Parser which would understand clipboard data and if it's filepath try to load it with File API and put in on canvas

summary_to_eng: Undo on canvas
Text_Summa: Undo on canvas [~accountid:5b67bcd8e6dba529eefda937] wouldn't it be confusing to undo changes from multiple screens? Imagine you're working on canvas and made changes in several screens and now you're working on screen #4. You want to undo all changes in that screen but unintentionally will remove changes from other screens as well[~accountid:557058:7ae9d263-27ab-437c-9306-d8fad371f87c] we describe logic from canva. Do we really need to delete changes via cmd+Z between screens?[~accountid:5b67bcd8e6dba529eefda937][~accountid:557058:1ea93978-7189-478c-802a-3ba4422731a6] We need ctrl-z option that works across all canvases in the lesson. As described in the user story.On the call with [~accountid:557058:1ea93978-7189-478c-802a-3ba4422731a6] we discussed blocker bug for Undo function. I approve that Daniyar will take this bug-issues In progress.Do we need to add in Undo function to delete created phase?# In the transition from canvas to preview mode and back frontend will save Undo-Redo history

summary_to_eng: Need to change logic of store images and file into AWS on frontend
Text_Summa: Need to change logic of store images and file into AWS on frontend {quote}[@nakusyat|https://teacherlyio.slack.com/team/UCAUM32CW] [@Gulya|https://teacherlyio.slack.com/team/UHWRS1HNK] [@Ulan Kozhomuratov|https://teacherlyio. slack.com/team/UDN1TE4SW] [@Dmitri Kononenko|https://teacherlyio.slack.com/team/UR0DY812Q] turns out it's not possible to download files from web and upload them to S3 all by frontend itself due to CORS policies on websites from which we try to fetch images and files. Most sites have CORS configured and neither {{fetch}} nor {{axios}} or any other frontend tool is able to retrieve content from those websites. Even though {{fetch}} has {{mode: no-cors}} and is able to perform request its data is opaque and isn't readable. I guess we have to come up with a solution for image / file upload from backend{quote}Won't be done. Already handled on the backend

Better to use google classroom API directly with php-client.# For students; I see Sign in with G Suite; but for students we added google sign-in without gsuite.[~accountid:557058:7ae9d263-27ab-437c-9306-d8fad371f87c] please confirm error message text[~accountid:557058:7ae9d263-27ab-437c-9306-d8fad371f87c]

summary_to_eng: Research about how to integrate Google SSO and GSuite
Text_Summa: Research about how to integrate Google SSO and GSuite We don't need actually Google SSO; we need to figure out how to sign-in through google account from GSuite.Need to add G Suite domain entity to organization.Access to Classroom API enabled by default for all teachers.Oauth2 scoops for Classrooms APIIn existing backend we have to implement [Google Sign-In|https://developers.google.com/identity/#google-sign-in]. Basic profile information is not enough; so in {{scope}} parameter we need to specify desired scopes of Classroom API.This [video|https://youtu.be/zZt8SFivjps] explains how authorization process works.

summary_to_eng: Optimize the database queryset in notifications controller
Text_Summa: Optimize the database queryset in notifications controller * In the research task; I had a couple of ideas on how to optimize query* Error occurred with team relationship. When there is no object; it cant get id and name. Really strange; because in cases with other relationships no object cases are being handled* Investigated how to optimize query even more[~accountid:557058:aa0d475c-712d-4039-803e-4f5df9c3da53] [~accountid:557058:4d51e61f-f264-4dac-b7cd-d45ab512d07e]* Read more and searched examples on using collection's has() method* Tried to first retrieve notifications and later in loop check for type_id and implode needed relation* Researched code in responses app within project; found some really good examples; that I could implement in my caseWhat was the payload before optimization (the entire payload consisting of 31 separate notifications)[~accountid:5b044dd827dd77348bacbf34] {{created_at}} missed; the rest is fine. did you just refactor notifications?[~accountid:557058:dc97fe24-bdda-4965-9046-7974ad38ae38] Thanks; created_at will add it now. Yes; so far only /notifications has been optimized[~accountid:5b044dd827dd77348bacbf34] [https://www.loom.com/share/b752002b79f74389ae38d8939faf944f|https://www.loom.com/share/b752002b79f74389ae38d8939faf944f] facebook seems to handle it this way too.[~accountid:557058:dc97fe24-bdda-4965-9046-7974ad38ae38] Yep; got it. In general; a cool idea; improvements will most likely be needed along the front. Now I'll think about how to implement it better on the back[~accountid:5b044dd827dd77348bacbf34] as far as I understand; laravel has its own pagination mechanism; for example; you can look at the point {{/api/teacher/lesson-templates}} ; but I don’t know how applicable it is after your optimizations for fetching data from the database[~accountid:557058:dc97fe24-bdda-4965-9046-7974ad38ae38] I studied a little how pagination is implemented at the point {{￼/api/teacher/lesson-template}}￼; as it is implemented there with my optimization it will not work. Also studied pagination in Laravel ([https://laravel.com/docs/7.x/pagination#paginating-query-builder-results|https://laravel.com/docs/7.x/pagination#paginating- query-builder-results]). From under the hood; too; will not work; it will be necessary to override'it a little but it is quite feasible. But in extreme cases; you can even do this: When loading the main one; load only the number of notifications; and then when you click on the bell; load all the notifications (on the front at this moment there will just be a loader)[~accountid:5b044dd827dd77348bacbf34] according to the numbers; what I see is a good optimization. Put your branch in development; let's test it. In parallel; you can prepare MP.* Investigated how respinses work in project; read the documentation

summary_to_eng: Wrong link "go to classes" on the student invite page
Text_Summa: Wrong link "go to classes" on the student invite page # Open [https://student-staging.teacherly.io/password/reset|https://student-staging.teacherly.io/password/reset][~accountid:5b67bcd8e6dba529eefda937] Here is the old student logic. We need to decide what to do here. Probably; if the user is already authenticated and clicks on the invitation link again; then he should be redirected to the student room without any “go to classes”. And if someone tries to request a url with a non-existent token; then I would throw a 403 or redirect to the login page; not the wrong token.[~accountid:5cee2d23919eaf0f2135ac64] don't fully understand the problem. Can we sync for 10 minutes?Agreed to do the next check. If the user is not authorized and the reset token is valid; then we log in and redirect to the student immediately. If the user is not authorized and the token does not exist; then we redirect to the root page with logins. If the user is authorized; then to the student.After the student has passed the activation of the invite; he is redirected to the student dashboard. Since we cannot login a user from one dashboard to another; the student gets to the login form.Checked fix. Now the user redirects on the main page and doesn't confuse when he/she saw Invalid token message previously.

summary_to_eng: 10.2 - Whiteboard feature
Text_Summa: 10.2 - Whiteboard feature {quote}It's the action; when a teacher starts activity; it means that every student should have their own phase with the whiteboard toolbar enabled to draw; text etc… to complete teacher's tasks. Teacher can start activity and stop activity. After stopping activity on the student's side; the whiteboard toolbar should be blocked and all data(drawings; etc) should be stored inside the student's phase. Teacher should see students' phases and check them all. It could be attached to the student's camera view; or it could be a separate module or block with these phases.{quote}The most time efficient for the whiteboard feature is [https://zwibbler.com/|https://zwibbler.com/] it costs $3499 USD and it is only whiteboard library. It doesn't include screen broadcasting; chat and recording.

With disabled xdebug php performance increased by ~30%.[~accountid:5cee2d23919eaf0f2135ac64] [~accountid:557058:49abf63e-994b-4f7b-9758-23477860728f]Disable xdebug by default [https://lumicislate.atlassian.net/browse/TILT-7823|https://lumicislate.atlassian.net/browse/TILT-7823|smart-link] . To apply changes; pull from production branch and rebuild api image. Also view xdebug section in README.mdPulled latest changes from production branch. Also can you just run only api; mysql and redis services and run tests.[~accountid:5cee2d23919eaf0f2135ac64] I have finally resolved tests issue. All project related settings can be placed in {{config/settings.php}} file.

We already use it for populating database in tests. For populating data for developers/staging environment we can have standalone database seeder class; to prevent running collisions in test runs. When we can populate all data in staging/dev with single command like {{php artisan db:seed --class=StagingSeeder}}[~accountid:5b67bcd8e6dba529eefda937] can you make a loom and show me how ATL skills data used in platform?[~accountid:5cee2d23919eaf0f2135ac64] [https://www.loom.com/share/f83b6ecd366d4b30ad43c0f15534e780|https://www.loom.com/share/f83b6ecd366d4b30ad43c0f15534e780][~accountid:5b67bcd8e6dba529eefda937] Other tables holds a lot of data and it messy. I can't figure out which data we really need for testing. And can't add it as is thought seeders; because it a lot (thousands of rows). I can set up a completely fresh environment with current seeders and when we sync and think what we need to add. summary_to_eng: Zero Date, Datetime, and Timestamp values
Text_Summa: Zero Date, Datetime, and Timestamp values Found in laravel docs. Starting with MySQL 5.7; {{0000-00-00 00:00:00}} is no longer considered a valid date. As documented at the [+Laravel 5.2 upgrade guide+|https://laravel.com/docs/5.2/upgrade#upgrade-5.2.0]; all timestamp columns should receive a valid default value when you insert records into your database. You may use the {{useCurrent()}} column modifier (from Laravel 5.1.25 and above) in your migrations to default the timestamp columns to the current timestamps; or you may make the timestamps {{nullable()}} to allow null values.

summary_to_eng: Add coloring of linked user cards
Text_Summa: Add coloring of linked user cards [~takt911] Coloring the linked map is done in such a way; in the appendix there is a list with a color palette of 10 gradients; we sum the last 4 digits of the map and take the remainder of the division by 10; as a result we get a number from 0 to 9; which we substitute into our list with palettes and pull out the gradient. Thus; on different phones under the same account in the application; the same card will be painted with the same color; but unfortunately there may be duplicate colors; but I think that is rare. Do you like this logic of card coloring?[~pavel] Ok; I'll have to test it; users usually don't have many cards; but even then there is a risk that; for example; only 2 cards are tied up and both will be in the same colorcards are displayed in the color that is attached to them. all OK

summary_to_eng: Learn / work on loading, saving and displaying images from S3
Text_Summa: Learn / work on loading, saving and displaying images from S3 The most optimal scenario would be: generating a pre-signed url on the server and returning them to the client; so that the client requests resources (photos) in s3 directly - it will remove the load from the server and without an intermediary in the face of the server; loading resources (images) from clients should be faster .

summary_to_eng: Connect postgres database to the project (local for now)

I came across in the dock on different ways to connect psycopg2 (the module is necessary for Django to work with postgresql). There is a way to binarize locally and use it in a project and a way to easily install via pip; but it is not recommended for production according to the docks. Studied the differences to take into account in the futureConnected postgresql in docker container. Did a little research on the discussions on the difference between psycopg2-binary and building a binary and using it as an external command. In the future; psycopg2 will not be installed by pip together with the binary; it will need to be built separately (we will take into account when building the docker image with the project)

summary_to_eng: MIC-301 Social login networks
Text_Summa: MIC-301 Social login networks Authorization through Google cannot be done simply through allauth. The user will have to redirect to apihi and the api will have to record the session. You should not do this; because in this case; for some users we will have authorization by tokens without sessions; and for others without tokens; but with sessions. You will need to dig into the doc: [https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/OAuth2WebServer] and integrate it into our token authorization process. Unfortunately there is no obvious documentation in the rest-auth docThen I searched / studied different packages for authorization by social networks. networks; trying to apply a solution that authorized only by tokens; avoiding sessions. I even started to implement an authorization service that absolutely does not save state and does not use sessions; having previously tried to find similar solutions on the Internet - I did not find it. As a result; I quit this case; because I came to the conclusion that the solution is absolutely pointless and I did not find a similar solution in Google for this very reason.

summary_to_eng: Server authorization for production
Text_Summa: Server authorization for production Communication with Dmitry Kononenko and Belek in the slack regarding access to the server and deadlines for the task.Research on adding basic auth:created a directory in /opt/docker/nginx/.htpasswd there the citycam.kg file forwarded the folder as a volume ./htpasswd:/etc/nginx/.htpasswd stopped containers re-uploaded basic auth does not work looking for a reason.Studying the cause of the Serer error 503. Judging by the logs:Communication with developers about 503 errors. It arose after the deployment to the citycam.kg serverchanged files in opt docker config; tried to place them in the htpasswd directory as recommended in the documentation [https://github.com/jwilder/nginx-proxy] and restarted containers in vhost studied default and default.conf configs. In the default file; I changed the value of auth_basic; but after restarting the container; the value I entered is overwritten. As a result; basic authorization does not work.Communication with developers about fixing ci/cd deployment and application code on citycam.kgAfter restarting the deployment and fixing the ci/cd variables in Gitlab 503; the error disappeared. Also; after editing the citycam.kg file by Belek; the authorization worked.

summary_to_eng: API - Web Create account
Text_Summa: API - Web Create account [~alexander.medvedev] is waiting for [~vasily.toropchin] update on doc he needAdd validation for sign-up fieldsAdd password validation for at least 6 charactersFrom SamatCustomer: [https://gitlab.com/sortedhouse/backend/blob/develop/docs/api.md#sign-up-1]https://pm.maddevs.co/browse/SOR-29?focusedCommentId=65781&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-65781https://pm.maddevs.co/browse/SOR-29?focusedCommentId=66427&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-66427The reason i reopened the ticket is to review one issue related to _*Terms and Condition acceptance*_. By the business requirements _Terms and Condition_ should be accepted by a user; so as we have the Terms and Condition acceptance step is the last and there could a case when the sign-up process could be terminated by accident. But on the previous steps all filled in data are saved; so further a user without acceptance can already sign-in and use the services at all.[~kairat] the simplest way to solve it is adding one more attribute to a response after sign-in. It would be a boolean attribute; which described have users accept the terms or not. Then the frontend can add a message to users about this state. And disable functions if it's needed.another issue is there is no endpoint of customers to specify which kind of notification to receive - email; sms or both.in docs i cant find the way to specify to accept terms by a customer. if there is the way; so which endpoint is that?sign in endpoint is broken now; it is returning 404for customer there is no way to save addressthere is an issue of signup endpoint; the password field is throwing error - password must be 6 chars even if send "Hello2012".[~kairat] and [~samat.jukeshov] here is the documents for Customer Registration End Points:when trying to sign up with data:customer signup* Updated documentation for Customer Sign up [https://gitlab.com/sortedhouse/backend/blob/feature/SOR-30/docs/api.md#sign-up]

Could you resend the correct link please?please check in figma without prototype{panel:title=From Saul}[~samat.jukeshov]PROVIDER SIGNUP[~alex] I don't see the following changes have been done:Design is good; just one question. Since a provider could be a big company who have a number of divisions; they may offer multiple services which different people work for. Eg they have a garden division who can work in a 50 mile radius of NE32 5JA but also have a plumber who can only work in a 25 mile radius of NE32 5XZ. How is this shown to the provider within their account; so they know the right radius is selected for the right service; or if they want to increase or decrease the radius?ready; steady; go

Text_Summa: Feedback on our production [~iain] please clarify the following feedback:one. **[Maksim Gacheskiy|https://gitlab.com/HEKTOdaleky] mentioned this issue in [a merge request of sortedhouse/frontend|https://gitlab.com/sortedhouse/frontend/-/merge_requests/90]:[Maksim Gacheskiy|https://gitlab.com/HEKTOdaleky] mentioned this issue in [a commit of sortedhouse/frontend|https://gitlab.com/sortedhouse/frontend/-/commit/2b2e656dfc045655e10f78886b9245a1d6d01e37]:[~iain] what about:[Maksim Gacheskiy|https://gitlab.com/HEKTOdaleky] mentioned this issue in [a commit of sortedhouse/frontend|https://gitlab.com/sortedhouse/frontend/-/commit/72536b17b653304e7feccfb953d2bace4129dc0e]:[Maksim Gacheskiy|https://gitlab.com/HEKTOdaleky] mentioned this issue in [a commit of sortedhouse/frontend|https://gitlab.com/sortedhouse/frontend/-/commit/07fbd8a0b750d7a8eb16e348d63face6ee977130]:[Maksim Gacheskiy|https://gitlab.com/HEKTOdaleky] mentioned this issue in [a commit of sortedhouse/frontend|https://gitlab.com/sortedhouse/frontend/-/commit/f7d4022f94c5ca858b426300667fd1b35c6db27d]:[Maksim Gacheskiy|https://gitlab.com/HEKTOdaleky] mentioned this issue in [a commit of sortedhouse/frontend|https://gitlab.com/sortedhouse/frontend/-/commit/cad3d81304e408138abaede1c1c36fc268202c25]:# Apologies if there has been confusion caused on this with my explanation. If you would rather we discuss it on Friday so we are clear; we will be happy to do so. I will try and explain more what I mean here though to give you a better idea. I have attached an example which is extremely common for address entry on a website. You can see that Postcode is asked for first; and they have the option to find address; which then normally just requires a user to enter their door number/building name. I know we don't have that functionality (as I presume it is a paid extra) and I am also aware that full postcode is our primary piece of information. However; the current format used in the design is confusing in its layout. Can we add the individual cells for each part of the address (as shown in the attachment) and make them all mandatory; keeping postcode entry first? It is clear to the User that they need to give us the full address and prevents a confusing UX (it wasn't clear to me how to write the full address into the cell in the current design)._!Sorted House - Address Example .JPG|width=402;height=389! _only 1 sub-ticket is waiting for resolution. Forced Vasiliy to do this todayLGTM

summary_to_eng: Set up Google Analytics Enhanced Ecommerce with GTM and IT for ALL TRANSACTIONS
Text_Summa: Set up Google Analytics Enhanced Ecommerce with GTM and IT for ALL TRANSACTIONS As we discuss today; this task will start from 21 Feb2020; and finish on 24 Feb2020[ ~huongbn@topica.edu.vn ] this task may take time. a lot of things to do.[ ~ducnh2@topica.edu.vn ] Today let me know your estimated time for finishing this task; okay?We need to set up GA Enhanced Ecommerce for 2 parts of products:[~hungcm] [~tuanlq] pls help us on this task.[ ~ducnh2@topica.edu.vn ]: discuss with [~tuanlq] or [~hungcm] to estimate deadline for this task today[ ~leonov.rs@gmail.com ] we setup EEC on our webiste; now you can view some ecommerce reports in Google Analytic; please check at 'Only Edumall.vn' viewGive me details please:this task seems much more complicated than expected. Someone set up EEC for edumall.vn about 1 year ago but it seems not set up correctly and the data is very different from what we have in our database.How do you think how much time do you need?These are the following steps that we will take to fully integrate enhanced eCommerce:[ ~anhdn16@topica.edu.vn ] any sub-tasks on that?[ ~anhdn16@topica.edu.vn ] hi; create subtasks please for each of these steps. It would be better to track this task.[~hungcm] [~hoangld2] we need IT helps to finish this task. pls take time to discuss with us.[~tuanlq] pay your attention please. We have discussed this task with you today.[~hoangld2] em check cái này nhé. bị miss lấu quá rồi.[~hoangld2] task nay la highest priority. ấp dung JOc.30 (4-12-24) triệt để nhé.[ ~anhdn16@topica.edu.vn ] follow kĩ task này điHey all. summary_to_eng: Can't play video in Kelley
Text_Summa: Can't play video in Kelley !Screen Shot 2020-04-24 at 21.07.27.png![~azat17] I see this error when click Play button.I chased for this error locally and in the end the result seemed to be the same as i supposed earlier. The error appears because in preview.js script at the line 46 it gets the url value from href attribute like so var href = $(this).attr('href') and tries to do this replacing action href = href.replace( /d1mjfb268gelin.cloudfront.net/g; "daevt1q1a24kq.cloudfront.net"). This action are being taken on the element with class equal to .lecture-preview. But its content can either have or not have the href attribute based on its asset_type field. When asset_type field's value is other than 'Video' then the .lecture-preview element remain without href element and replacing function is executed on the href attribute which's null.FYI the test staging for Kelley is http://kelley2-staging.edumall.io/[~azat17]: in case lecture does not have video url; we should display an error notification. It'll help user avoid confusing when use.This task is frozen because we are moving Azat to https://jira.topica.vn/browse/ETBA-58[~ducla5]; re-assigned this one to youBecause field asset_type have value is "HTML" when user upload video so that we can't play video. Change value to "Video" will resolve this issue.

But i wonder how it's was set up with wrong type(HTML) for some video lectures; i think admins might have done a typo. But anyway; in production database we have some amount of courses with videos with broken video players; that's as it was mentioned before either because of this wrong type or because of transcoding issues. I suggest to write a rake script; with running which we can set up the right value to asset_type field for Lectures with existing videos but some of them may not be working because they might have transcoding errors for which we can apply the button that we suggested by you !Screen Shot 2020-05-04 at 12.51.10.png![~azat17] The final target of this task is we need to add retranscode in web version.[~ducla5] "I mean wrong asset_type in code" - there is nothing wrong with asset_type in code. Please look at EVAB-283 branch. summary_to_eng: Cannot reset my password
Text_Summa: Cannot reset my password [~ducla5] Researched reset password functionality. Checked it in staging and prod. There appears an error in both Prod and Staging. After clicking on "Forgot password?" link I was redirected to AccountKit page. Researched AccountKit service. I turns out that AccountKit is the Facebook's service for authentication without using passwords. AccountKit's workflow is as follow it uses emails and phone numbers where it sends codes; after which a user should enter that code and if the code is valid a user gets redirected back to their page where special callback handlers handle the data with user's token. If everything in that workflow is ok the page for changing password is opened and a user will be able to type new password.[~ducla5][~ducla5] we use gmail for sending letters but gmail restricts us to send 500 letter in a day. I consider we should choose mailing services such as SendGrid. But as for now gmail should work fine but it's going to restrict us further.I'll create a SendGrid account for you.{code:java}[~ducla5] I already use these credentials for mailing[~azat17] where have you deployed? it's in staging?[~ducla5] yes. It's on stagingI confirm it works on stagingAbout the From field of email; can we change it to [ noreply@edumall.vn |mailto: noreply@edumall.vn ] or something; but not edumall@example.com ?Sure; I'll do it[~ducla5]; please check it as wellPlease change the subject of email to:[~ducla5] it can be checked both in staging and production

summary_to_eng: Join files JS together to optimize requests numbers
Text_Summa: Join files JS together to optimize requests numbers There are a lot of JS files that are not minified and not merged. Actually I would like to have all JS files minified and merged in 2-5 files (or more); but not 100+ like we have now; this is insane. Also I see some js files loading but they are the same.default bundling/merging/minification (+10 points on average)Regarding js optimizarion; I suggest to use builtin functionality. I performed bundle optimization and resulting bundle size is 2 times lower then with standard settings. Total number of js requests changed from 200 to 20. With this approach we will not rely on 3rd party solution; which is always good; since it does not increase overall system complexity - less possible bugs; less dev time wasted.[~denis.petrov] agreedTalking about the score; avg result will be between what we have with default setting(50); and with APO module(65). So between 50-65.[ ~puzanov@gmail.com ]; no; with built-in functionality we do not need to perform any additional work. Text_Summa: Discount function in online payment We have third party service where this landing gets info from. For base url of this service is the same as this site. For example in production there is a request being made for this url [https://epayment.edumall.co.th/api/courses] to grab courses' info also there're some discount values ​​being returned from this request. I checked Meduza in case if it's that service but it isn't. Also reading the code i found that some part of the payment are being made in that service so i need to know it and look at it's code. In main.js at 200 the line there is a call to complete a payment.[~peerapat] can you please give info about the service from your screenshot ? What's the service and maybe you have a link to the repository? I guess it's the service where the requests mentioned above are being sent toYou can access below link:A few updates. Found that data of courses that the site receives are being taken from meduza. Also figured out that discount amount exists in that data. Also figured out that this [https://git.edumall.io/edumalltl/e-payment] java service gets parameters from lending to complete a payment and that params include Omise token and the rest of the payment process is handled by [e -payment|https://git.edumall.io/edumalltl/e-payment] service. All that we need to do is go send that discount to [e-payment|https://git.edumall.io/edumalltl/e-payment] service as an additional parameter and change the amount of the price considering that discount.[~peerapat] should the discount from your screen be directly deducted from the price as a certain value or it's a percentage that should be deducted from the price ? In your screen it's 50. Does it mean that we should deduct 50 from the price ?[~peerapat] we also currently do not have discount information displayed on the page . I think we should display it somewhere; right? If so; can you please suggest where it should be. For example for chinesetoday-english.edumall.co.th it's 50. But user knows nothing about it on the assumption of UI[~azat17][~pornprappa] thanks! But what about this 65% mentioned above ? Is it calculated in the code now or do you set the pre-calculated corresponding prices directly in dashboard? I mean 2;799 THB and 990 THB[~pornprapa] do you know if staging version of landing e-payment ([http://edumalltl-etl-epayment-gate-web-staging.tsts.edumall.io/payment-option-v5.html|http:/ /edumalltl-etl-epayment-gate-web-staging.tsts.edumall.io/payment-option-v5.html?domain=testlandingpageit06.edumall.co.th&cid=5ea4069a450173000d000000&course_id=BC.hungdv2.test.01]) uses sandbox payments or it charges real payments? Has anyone used it before?[~azat17] about the price[~azat17] normally in the staging is the sandbox payment; we use [https://www.omise.co/api-testing] to test[~pornprapa] [~saran] could someone generate such a link co.th&cid=5ea4069a450173000d000000&course_id=BC.hungdv2.test.01] with valid cid ?[~Yann] [~ducla5] Could you please help provide the access (and support) as [~azat17] requested?{code:java}Got an access to Marol's staging database. Created Contactc3 and changed the prices and discount amounts for Landing testlandingpageit06.edumall.co.th for testing purposes. During that process faced validation errors due to some invalid parameters of my Contactc3; i fixed all that points. All the data were relevant and the eventual charged price was the amount with discount deducted from the original price. But all the testing data including contactc3 were generated manually by me. See the last 5 screenshots. Need to get automatically generated link to e-payment page to test all that flow again.[~saran] [~pornprappa][~azat17] let use this domain:[~ducla5] [~saran][~azat17] Awesome.[~azat17] I'll contact you via Slack for deploy time[ ~phatchaporn@topica.asia ] made a payment and got an error which i couldn't replicate in staging. Need to get access to Omise dashboard and void this payment ie made refund. summary_to_eng: Meaning of COD Leads with Complete Status
Text_Summa: Meaning of COD Leads with Complete Status [~saran] [~Yann]There are two main type of lead (C3) shown in Minerva; c3_cod and c3_credit.Explored the code; looked for all pieces of code that could change e-payment status of c3_cod leads. Looked at Minerva and Marol. And found that such operations could be done in Marol; all other places doesn't seem to be related to it. Especially found update_payment_status method in app/controllers/contact_api_controller line 73. Third party services can change the type of the contactc3 by sending request to that action method passing the id and status of the contactc3 in parameters. If we send "complete" status for a contactc3 there will be a check for if there are other contactc3s with the same email; course_id; in case there are then all that contactc3s will have their statuses changed to "completed" and some of them may have type equal to c3_cod. That's what i managed to find[~azat17] Do we know what is the third party service that you mentioned?[~pornprapa] see the message above please[~saran] it's e-payment backend service; e-payment landing the ones i know so farIs it the same e-payment service that we are currently using?[~saran] Yes; it's the same we are using now. Also i'm not fully sure if other landings may or may not send this request to change the status.[~azat17] Any suggested solution to prevent this; I think it is not correct to have c3_cod with complete status in our database.[~saran] we can add a clause in that request by which not to take duplicated contactc3 which have c3_cod type . Such way i can prevent status updating of c3_cod leads in that request and further see if we get any c3_cod with complete status or not.[~azat17] Sounds good.[~saran] I will not affect other flow. It mustn't do thatAs I discussed with [~azat17]; I think this ticket is ready to deploy.

summary_to_eng: The system did not change the status of some leads from incomplete to timeout
Text_Summa: The system did not change the status of some leads from incomplete to timeout Normally; Lead type "c3_credit" has 4 main e-payment status. (Ideally; it should be like to logic below)Went through Minerva; Marol and e-payment applications. Didn't find any code; especially background jobs (crons) that would handle functionality of changing statuses. Found schedulers in e-payment java service and started to investigate it; it also has requests to Marol. But figured out that requests are for changing Ibanking status. Still need to look for this functionality[~Yann] FYI. A few updates.[~azat17] Please note that this issue occurs only a few percent. Most of the contacts status were changed correctly.Had a call with Saran. Regarding this task as i mentioned before the problem of updating statuses occurs because some Contactc3s have priority equal to 3. Found that js landing ([https://git.edumall.io/edumalltl/etl-epayment-gate]) sends a request to change priority to 3 when Omise returns failure response when a user does payments. I consider that some percent of contactc3 had an error returned from Omise. It can happen when the submitted data is incorrect or outdated (card number; cvv; expiration date) or when there isn't enough money on the cardThank you [~azat17].[~saran] sure; okay[~saran] Actually it was a research ticket. I spent the time investigating how does the system change statuses to timeout and found the reason why some leads have their statuses not changed to timeout due to priority being equal to 3. There is nothing to deploy here[~azat17] Could you give me a bit more detail?[~saran][~azat17] From your third answer (3); if the customer got 3 as their priority; why does it changed to failed?[~saran] You mean why despite having priority equal to 3 it doesn't change status to failed ? Correct me please if i'm wrong[~azat17] Correct.[~saran] let me research it

summary_to_eng: LMS issues - investigate and fix
Text_Summa: LMS issues - investigate and fix Here's our assumption at the moment.Checked all sidekiq workers whether they consume too much resources or not. Sidekiq was fine and we didn't notice huge memory consumption by it. We checked unicorn server and its configs. During the timeout we didn't see that unicorn consumes too much memory however it wasn't giving a response so afterwards we decided to increase the number of unicorn workers to 9 and reduced the request timeout speed from 600 sec to 30 sec. It helped now. If this issue happens again we're going to increase the number of unicorn workers and see how it affects the memory and plan our next stepsconfirm.[~ducla5] yeah; right. I hope we find the root. It couldn't have appeared from nothing because it used to be ok in previous weeks

After applying new rule; both frontend and api will send old prices until reindexing occurs. Magento re-indexes invalid indexers every minute. Indexing time of catalogrule_rule and catalog_product_price depends on: number of active price rules; rules complexity; number of products; server resources. summary_to_eng: Tracking button in payment page
Text_Summa: Tracking button in payment page Checking the flow of COD and exploring how java e-payment service handles it.[~saran] [~pornprapa] I found that landing payment service after choosing COD sends requests toThank you [~azat17].[~saran] thanks. I think I'm going to handle it on my own. I found that an error appears before the request to the contactc3's status. I manage to fix that error then contacts' statuses should work corretlyDuring debugging the request of changing type of contactc3 i found that the request itself works fine. But for some landings there appears an error because ContactLDP becomes null. It happens sometimes during parsing price of courses. But the most funny part of this functionality was that if a user chooses COD payment and clicks on submit button they would always be redirected to cod-v5.html "thank you" page; no matter if the payment was successful or failure and users would think that everything is right. I now changed that logic in frontend and it shows error page with error messages[~azat17]Had a call with Saran where we discussed the current state of this ticket.The status was changed to c3_code correctly.You are welcome! Does that mean that i can close this issue ?[~azat17] Issue closed.
